# Definition of Done

> ⚠️ **Stub — Phase 1.** Full DoD checklist arrives in Phase 1.

A feature, refactor, or bug fix is **done** when every box below is
ticked. The Reviewer subagent runs this checklist before signing off.

Lines marked **(auto)** are enforced by `scripts/verify`; lines marked
**(manual)** require the Reviewer's eye.

## Mechanical (auto-enforced)

- [ ] **(auto)** Format check passes (`cadence.yaml` `commands.format`)
- [ ] **(auto)** Lint passes (`cadence.yaml` `commands.lint`)
- [ ] **(auto)** Boundary check passes (`tool/check_boundaries.py`)
- [ ] **(auto)** Tests pass (`cadence.yaml` `commands.test`)
- [ ] **(auto)** `scripts/verify` exits zero

## Architecture (manual — Reviewer cites the rule)

- [ ] Files placed per `docs/PATTERNS.md` §1 layer rules
- [ ] Controller uses the right shape per `docs/PATTERNS.md` §2
- [ ] No direct repository/source imports from features
- [ ] Every new service method has a corresponding narrow provider

## Patterns (manual — Reviewer cites the ADR)

- [ ] Mutations follow the optimistic-then-write ADR (or document the
      exception)
- [ ] Models live under `domain/models/` per ADR
- [ ] Every mutation has an error path per the error-surface ADR
- [ ] UI fire-and-forget calls wrapped per the UI-async ADR

## Tests (manual — Reviewer counts)

- [ ] One happy-path test per public controller method
- [ ] At least one edge case per public method
- [ ] One sequence test (≥3 mutations in order)
- [ ] One error test if the method has an error path
- [ ] Every mutation test asserts both state AND the write log

## Documentation

- [ ] New judgment calls get a new ADR
- [ ] New patterns are added to `PATTERNS.md`
- [ ] New gates are added to `cadence.yaml` or `analysis_options`
- [ ] `FRAMEWORK_CHANGELOG.md` has a new entry for any of the above

## Retrospective

- [ ] If the Reviewer caught any issue that *should* have been
      auto-enforced, a follow-up item is filed (or fixed in this PR)
- [ ] If a teammate had to make a judgment call not covered by ADRs,
      it's surfaced for the retrospective

## Sign-off

```
Reviewer sign-off: all DoD boxes ticked.
Framework gaps: <list, or "none">
Recommended retrospective items: <list, or "none">
```
